      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study (refinement ratio r=1.5) conducted across all five COU operating points. GCI methodology per Celik et al. 2008 applied; GCI_fine for NIH QoI = 3.4% (worst case across operating points), well below the 5% threshold. Asymptotic range confirmed (ratio 0.99–1.02). Temporal discretization assessed via halving time-step; change in cycle-averaged NIH < 0.8%.",
      "acceptanceCriteria": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/morrison/ac/discretization-error-mrl2",
        "type": "AcceptanceCriteria",
        "name": "Discretization error acceptance criterion — MRL 2",
        "description": "GCI_fine < 5% for primary QoI (NIH) at all operating points. Achieved GCI_fine = 3.4% maximum; criterion met. Gradation 3 achieved due to formal GCI analysis with asymptotic range confirmation at all five operating conditions."
