    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "At MRL 2 for this COU, numerical solver error beyond discretization error (already assessed) is scoped out. The commercial solver's iterative convergence is monitored via residual norms (all below 1e-5) and mass imbalance (< 0.01%), providing sufficient confidence that solver error is negligible relative to discretization and model-form uncertainties. Formal separate solver error quantification is not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Use error is scoped out at MRL 2 for this COU. Simulation inputs were reviewed by a second analyst and all boundary conditions, material properties, and solver settings were independently verified against the simulation plan document prior to execution. A simulation checklist was completed and archived. Formal use-error assessment beyond peer review of inputs is not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Formal model-form uncertainty quantification is scoped out at MRL 2. The RANS k-omega SST turbulence model with power-law hemolysis damage accumulation (Giersiepen correlation) is the accepted standard approach for pump hemolysis CFD per FDA benchmark study findings. The validation activities at identical conditions provide indirect evidence of acceptable model form adequacy, which is sufficient at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "scoped-out",
      "rationale": "Formal parametric uncertainty propagation for model inputs is scoped out at MRL 2. Key inputs (fluid viscosity, density, pump geometry dimensions) were measured and their nominal values confirmed within specification. Boundary condition uncertainty (±5% flow rate, ±2% speed) was propagated through Monte Carlo analysis as part of the validation uncertainty quantification, providing adequate input uncertainty coverage at MRL 2."
    },
